49namespace WebKit {
50namespace NetworkCache {
51
52struct GlobalFrameID {
53 WebPageProxyIdentifier webPageProxyID;
54 WebCore::PageIdentifier webPageID;
55 WebCore::FrameIdentifier frameID;
56
57 unsigned hash() const;
58};
59
60inline unsigned GlobalFrameID::hash() const
61{
62 return computeHash(webPageID, frameID);
63}
64
65inline bool operator==(const GlobalFrameID& a, const GlobalFrameID& b)
66{
67 // No need to check webPageProxyID since webPageIDs are globally unique and a given WebPage is always
68 // associated with the same WebPageProxy.
69 return a.webPageID == b.webPageID && a.frameID == b.frameID;
70}
71
72}
73}
74
75namespace WTF {
76
77struct GlobalFrameIDHash {
78 static unsigned hash(const WebKit::NetworkCache::GlobalFrameID& key) { return key.hash(); }
79 static bool equal(const WebKit::NetworkCache::GlobalFrameID& a, const WebKit::NetworkCache::GlobalFrameID& b) { return a == b; }
80 static const bool safeToCompareToEmptyOrDeleted = true;
81};
82
83template<> struct HashTraits<WebKit::NetworkCache::GlobalFrameID> : GenericHashTraits<WebKit::NetworkCache::GlobalFrameID> {
84 static WebKit::NetworkCache::GlobalFrameID emptyValue() { return { }; }
85
86 static void constructDeletedValue(WebKit::NetworkCache::GlobalFrameID& slot) { new (NotNull, &slot.webPageID) WebCore::PageIdentifier(WTF::HashTableDeletedValue); }
87
88 static bool isDeletedValue(const WebKit::NetworkCache::GlobalFrameID& slot) { return slot.webPageID.isHashTableDeletedValue(); }
89};
90
91template<> struct DefaultHash<WebKit::NetworkCache::GlobalFrameID> : GlobalFrameIDHash { };
92
93}

112enum class RetrieveDecision {
113 Yes,
114 NoDueToHTTPMethod,
115 NoDueToConditionalRequest,
116 NoDueToReloadIgnoringCache,
117 NoDueToStreamingMedia,
118};
119
120enum class StoreDecision {
121 Yes,
122 NoDueToProtocol,
123 NoDueToHTTPMethod,
124 NoDueToNoStoreResponse,
125 NoDueToHTTPStatusCode,
126 NoDueToNoStoreRequest,
127 NoDueToUnlikelyToReuse,
128 NoDueToStreamingMedia,
129};
130
131enum class UseDecision {
132 Use,
133 Validate,
134 AsyncRevalidate,
135 NoDueToVaryingHeaderMismatch,
136 NoDueToMissingValidatorFields,
137 NoDueToDecodeFailure,
138 NoDueToExpiredRedirect
139};
140
141enum class CacheOption : uint8_t {
142 // In testing mode we try to eliminate sources of randomness. Cache does not shrink and there are no read timeouts.
143 TestingMode = 1 << 0,
144 RegisterNotify = 1 << 1,
145#if ENABLE(NETWORK_CACHE_SPECULATIVE_REVALIDATION)
146 SpeculativeRevalidation = 1 << 2,
147#endif
148};
149
150class Cache : public RefCounted<Cache> {
151public:
152 static RefPtr<Cache> open(NetworkProcess&, const String& cachePath, OptionSet<CacheOption>, PAL::SessionID);
153
154 size_t capacity() const;
155 void updateCapacity();
156
157 // Completion handler may get called back synchronously on failure.
158 struct RetrieveInfo {
159 MonotonicTime startTime;
160 MonotonicTime completionTime;
161 unsigned priority;
162 Storage::Timings storageTimings;
163 bool wasSpeculativeLoad { false };
164
165 WTF_MAKE_FAST_ALLOCATED;
166 };
167 using RetrieveCompletionHandler = Function<void(std::unique_ptr<Entry>, const RetrieveInfo&)>;
168 void retrieve(const WebCore::ResourceRequest&, const GlobalFrameID&, std::optional<NavigatingToAppBoundDomain>, RetrieveCompletionHandler&&);
169 std::unique_ptr<Entry> store(const WebCore::ResourceRequest&, const WebCore::ResourceResponse&, RefPtr<WebCore::SharedBuffer>&&, Function<void(MappedBody&)>&& = nullptr);
170 std::unique_ptr<Entry> storeRedirect(const WebCore::ResourceRequest&, const WebCore::ResourceResponse&, const WebCore::ResourceRequest& redirectRequest, std::optional<Seconds> maxAgeCap);
171 std::unique_ptr<Entry> update(const WebCore::ResourceRequest&, const Entry&, const WebCore::ResourceResponse& validatingResponse);
172
173 struct TraversalEntry {
174 const Entry& entry;
175 const Storage::RecordInfo& recordInfo;
176 };
177 void traverse(Function<void(const TraversalEntry*)>&&);
178 void remove(const Key&);
179 void remove(const WebCore::ResourceRequest&);
180 void remove(const Vector<Key>&, Function<void()>&&);
181
182 void clear();
183 void clear(WallTime modifiedSince, Function<void()>&&);
184
185 void retrieveData(const DataKey&, Function<void(const uint8_t*, size_t)>);
186 void storeData(const DataKey&, const uint8_t* data, size_t);
187
188 std::unique_ptr<Entry> makeEntry(const WebCore::ResourceRequest&, const WebCore::ResourceResponse&, RefPtr<WebCore::SharedBuffer>&&);
189 std::unique_ptr<Entry> makeRedirectEntry(const WebCore::ResourceRequest&, const WebCore::ResourceResponse&, const WebCore::ResourceRequest& redirectRequest);
190
191 void dumpContentsToFile();
192
193 String recordsPathIsolatedCopy() const;
194
195#if ENABLE(NETWORK_CACHE_SPECULATIVE_REVALIDATION)
196 SpeculativeLoadManager* speculativeLoadManager() { return m_speculativeLoadManager.get(); }
197#endif
198
199#if ENABLE(NETWORK_CACHE_STALE_WHILE_REVALIDATE)
200 void startAsyncRevalidationIfNeeded(const WebCore::ResourceRequest&, const NetworkCache::Key&, std::unique_ptr<Entry>&&, const GlobalFrameID&, std::optional<NavigatingToAppBoundDomain>);
201#endif
202
203 void browsingContextRemoved(WebPageProxyIdentifier, WebCore::PageIdentifier, WebCore::FrameIdentifier);
204
205 NetworkProcess& networkProcess() { return m_networkProcess.get(); }
206 PAL::SessionID sessionID() const { return m_sessionID; }
207 const String& storageDirectory() const { return m_storageDirectory; }
208
209 ~Cache();
210
211private:
212 Cache(NetworkProcess&, const String& storageDirectory, Ref<Storage>&&, OptionSet<CacheOption>, PAL::SessionID);
213
214 Key makeCacheKey(const WebCore::ResourceRequest&);
215
216 static void completeRetrieve(RetrieveCompletionHandler&&, std::unique_ptr<Entry>, RetrieveInfo&);
217
218 String dumpFilePath() const;
219 void deleteDumpFile();
220
221 std::optional<Seconds> maxAgeCap(Entry&, const WebCore::ResourceRequest&, PAL::SessionID);
222
223 Ref<Storage> m_storage;
224 Ref<NetworkProcess> m_networkProcess;
225
226#if ENABLE(NETWORK_CACHE_SPECULATIVE_REVALIDATION)
227 std::unique_ptr<WebCore::LowPowerModeNotifier> m_lowPowerModeNotifier;
228 std::unique_ptr<SpeculativeLoadManager> m_speculativeLoadManager;
229#endif
230
231#if ENABLE(NETWORK_CACHE_STALE_WHILE_REVALIDATE)
232 HashMap<Key, std::unique_ptr<AsyncRevalidation>> m_pendingAsyncRevalidations;
233 HashMap<GlobalFrameID, WeakHashSet<AsyncRevalidation>> m_pendingAsyncRevalidationByPage;
234#endif
235
236 unsigned m_traverseCount { 0 };
237 PAL::SessionID m_sessionID;
238 String m_storageDirectory;
239};
